---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Volcanism — Geology Terms That Score Big"
  description="Volcano and geology words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. MAGMA 10pts, PYREX 17pts, BASALT 8pts, CALDERA 10pts. Volcanic vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble volcano words, geology scrabble terms, magma scrabble points, pyrex scrabble, basalt scrabble word, caldera scrabble, volcanic words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Volcanism — Geology Terms That Score Big","description":"Volcano and geology words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. MAGMA 10pts, PYREX 17pts, BASALT 8pts, CALDERA 10pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-volcanism"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is PYREX a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! PYREX scores 17 points (P=3, Y=4, R=1, E=1, X=8). While commonly known as a brand of heat-resistant glass, pyrex (lowercase) is valid in SOWPODS as a type of borosilicate glass. The X tile (8pts) and Y tile (4pts) deliver most of the scoring."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is MAGMA worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"MAGMA scores 10 points (M=3, A=1, G=2, M=3, A=1). It means molten rock beneath the Earth's surface. The two M tiles (3pts each) and G tile (2pts) provide the scoring power from this 5-letter word."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is BASALT valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. BASALT scores 8 points (B=3, A=1, S=1, A=1, L=1, T=1) and is the most common volcanic rock. The B tile (3pts) provides the main scoring contribution in this 6-letter word."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Volcanism — Geology Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Volcanic geology delivers explosive Scrabble scores. PYREX carries the X tile for 17 points, MAGMA doubles up on M tiles for 10, and everyday terms like BASALT and LAVA give you reliable plays. These earth science words combine premium consonants with familiar vocabulary.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PYREX (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MAGMA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CALDERA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BASALT</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Volcanic Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">PYREX — 17 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">P=3, Y=4, R=1, E=1, X=8 · 5 letters · X+Y+P power</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Heat-resistant borosilicate glass, originally developed to withstand volcanic-level temperatures. PYREX stacks three premium tiles (X=8, Y=4, P=3) for 17 points from 5 letters — a scorching 3.4 points per tile.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌋 MAGMA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · M=3, A=1, G=2, M=3, A=1 · Molten rock below surface</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🕳️ CALDERA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · C=3, A=1, L=1, D=2, E=1, R=1, A=1 · Volcanic crater</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪨 BASALT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · B=3, A=1, S=1, A=1, L=1, T=1 · Common volcanic rock</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔥 PUMICE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · P=3, U=1, M=3, I=1, C=3, E=1 · Porous volcanic glass</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Geological Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LAVA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TEPHRA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CRATER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MANTLE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VENT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CRUST</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Volcanic Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PYREX maximises the X tile:</span> At 17 points, PYREX outscores most X words. It needs only P, Y, R, E — three of which are semi-common. Keep this word in mind whenever X appears on your rack.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">MAGMA handles double-M racks:</span> Two Ms (3pts each) clog your rack. MAGMA clears both with common letters (A, G, A) for 10 points — and it's only 5 tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BASALT is a solid 6-letter base:</span> At 8 points and 6 tiles, BASALT won't win awards — but it uses B effectively and opens lanes for hooks (BASALTS, BASALTIC).</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Volcanic words solve the <span class="text-white font-medium">double-M and X tile problems</span> that plague many racks. MAGMA handles MM, PYREX handles X — and both are instantly recognisable words that won't slip your memory under tournament pressure.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-gemstones/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Gemstones</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-astronomy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Astronomy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words for Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid geology word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
